<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
    <meta charset="utf-8">

    <title><%=title%></title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="format-detection" content="telephone=no">

    <!-- Bootstrap -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//trevi.io/example/style.css">
</head>
<body>

<div class="bg-box">
    <div class="layer"></div>
</div>

<main class="fullpage main fullpage-wrapper"
      style="height: 100%; position: relative; top: 0px;transition: top 0ms ease 900ms; touch-action: none;">
    <section style="height: 906px; visibility: visible; opacity: 1;">
        <div class="section-content-wrapper container"
             style="padding-top: 50px; padding-bottom: 50px; overflow: hidden; display: table; height: 633px; margin-bottom: 0px;">
            <div class="section-content">
                <h1 class="section-main-title"><img src="./trevi_logo.png" alt="Trevi" style="max-width:100%;"></h1>

                <p class="lead">
                    Fast, light web application server framwork for Swift.<br>
                    Trevi uses an event-driven, non-blocking I/O model based on libuv.<br>
                    Trevi refers to node.js core modules and makes Trevi core modules similary to support Node.js features.<br>
                    Trevi also hopes that node.js developers easily use and develop Trevi.<br>
                    Swift 2.2 and xCode 7.1.1 required or latest release.<br>
                </p>
                <div class="btn"><a href="https://github.com/Trevi-Swift/Trevi">GitHub</a></div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="copyright">
            <p>Â© Trevi Foundation, 2015</p>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>
</body>
</html>

